  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Seeing this in v1.6.1.\r\n\r\n1. Create a Deployment and a Service\r\n\r\n```\r\n---\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nkind: Service\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: hello-openshift\r\nspec:\r\n  selector:\r\n    app: hello\r\n  ports:\r\n    - protocol: TCP\r\n      port: 80\r\n      targetPort: 80\r\n---\r\napiVersion: apps/v1beta1\r\nkind: Deployment\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: hello-openshift \r\nspec:\r\n  replicas: 1\r\n  template:\r\n    metadata:\r\n      labels:\r\n        app: hello\r\n    spec:\r\n      containers:\r\n      - name: hello-openshift\r\n        image: openshift/hello-openshift\r\n        ports:\r\n        - containerPort: 80\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. On the Deployment add an ownerRef that points back to the Service\r\n3. kubectl delete the Service\r\n\r\nThe Service and the Deployment are deleted, but the ReplicaSet and pods remain.  This is neither Orphan nor Foreground/Background policy. This behavior should never happen.\r\n\r\nNote: if I make a delete call to the API with propagationPolicy set explicitly then things behave as expected, so this only occurs when the resource's default propagation policy is being used.",
